		<description><![CDATA[a big part of syrian time is adopted from middle eastern culture though. the difference between polychronemic and monochronemic time orientation. it has to do with the Arabic culture that more than one thing is usually happening at once whereas one thing can only happen at a time in other cultures (America). I&#039;m sure that those who are concious of the appropriate times for tefila etc. are not following syrian time there.]]></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>a big part of syrian time is adopted from middle eastern culture though. the difference between polychronemic and monochronemic time orientation. it has to do with the Arabic culture that more than one thing is usually happening at once whereas one thing can only happen at a time in other cultures (America). I&#8217;m sure that those who are concious of the appropriate times for tefila etc. are not following syrian time there.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
