		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>A noteworthy addendum: </p>
<p>I recently heard an interesting lecture by Rabbi Miller, A&#8217;H. The basic premise was about time&#8211;specifically, punctuality. As Jews, he said, if we say Shema just a few seconds later than when we&#8217;re supposed to, then we completely miss out on the opportunity to fulfill the mitzvah. </p>
<p>The notion of &#8216;Syrian time&#8217; should not exist; it conflicts with the core of our religion. The only exception should be, of course, as the last commenter addressed, to utilize it in order to avoid danger.     </p>
<p>You can access Rabbi Miller&#8217;s class, as well as thousands of others, on <a href="http://www.learntorah.com" rel="nofollow">http://www.learntorah.com</a></p>
