	<item>
		<title>By: a random</title>
		<link>http://sypulse.org/wordpress/2011/08/11/syrian-time-what-time-is-it/#comment-53</link>
		<dc:creator>a random</dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Thu, 11 Aug 2011 17:30:48 +0000</pubDate>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://thesypulse.com/?p=299#comment-53</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[&quot;SY time&quot; was a necessary system used in the old country. Whenever people were having events like weddings or whatever they would set it for 5pm, which meant 8pm to all Syrian Jews. The point was to throw off malicious anti-semites. In those tough times it was a clutch way to party safely. Fortunately for Syrian Jews today we don&#039;t need such a system America. Despite our comfort, old habits die hard as we are still using this time trick to inadvertently confuse guests of other backgrounds.]]></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>&#8220;SY time&#8221; was a necessary system used in the old country. Whenever people were having events like weddings or whatever they would set it for 5pm, which meant 8pm to all Syrian Jews. The point was to throw off malicious anti-semites. In those tough times it was a clutch way to party safely. Fortunately for Syrian Jews today we don&#8217;t need such a system America. Despite our comfort, old habits die hard as we are still using this time trick to inadvertently confuse guests of other backgrounds.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
